<title>Introduction</title>

<screenshot>
  <screeninfo>&krusader; Logo</screeninfo>
  <mediaobject>
    <imageobject><imagedata fileref="krusader_title.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject>
    <imageobject><imagedata fileref="krusader_title.png" format="EPS"/></imageobject>
    <textobject><phrase>&krusader; Logo</phrase></textobject>
  </mediaobject>
</screenshot>

<para>&krusader; is an advanced, twin-panel, "commander"-style file-manager
			for &kde; 3.2.x (similar to <application>Midnight or Total Commander</application>)
			but with many extras.
			&krusader; offers all the file-management features you could possibly want, and more!</para>

<para>Plus: extensive Archive handling, mounted Filesystem support, &FTP;,
     advanced Search module, viewer/Editor, directory Synchronisation,
     file content Comparisons, powerful batch Renaming and much, much more.
			Supports archive formats: ace, arj, bzip2, gzip, iso, lha, rar, rpm, tar and zip.
     Handles other &kioslaves1_url; such as smb:// or fish://.</para>

<para>Almost completely customizable, very user friendly, fast,
			and looks great on your desktop! :-)</para>

<para>Give &krusader; a try.</para>


