<chapter id="features">
<title>Features</title>

<note><para>
The most important features are listed here. It would make this list too long if we were to
display all the features and improvements.
You can discover even more features in this documentation or in the &changelog_url; file.
</para></note>

<para>
<itemizedlist>
  <listitem>
     <para>Configurable &main_toolbar_lnk; and
           <link linkend="key_bindings">key-bindings</link>.</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
     <para>Full ace, arj, bzip2, gzip, iso, lha, rar, rpm, tar and zip support
     <link linkend="archives">support</link>.</para></listitem>
  <listitem>

      <para><link linkend="krusearcher">Advanced search module</link> that can search in archives.</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
      <para><link linkend="compare-dir">Directory comparison</link> and
            <link linkend="view-menu">filtering</link>.</para>
  </listitem>

   <listitem>
      <para><link linkend="panels">Quick View and Tree panels</link>.</para>
   </listitem>

  <listitem>
       <para>&FTP;/SAMBA client with a <link linkend="remote-man">connection manager</link>
             with SFTP/SCP support.</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
       <para>Open a <link linkend="commands-menu">terminal</link> to the browsed path.</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
       <para>Optional embedded &termemu_lnk;.</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
      <para>Configurable <link linkend="bookman">bookmark</link> list (using BookMan, the bookmark
      manager).</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
      <para>Easy editing of <link linkend="file-menu">file permissions</link>.</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
      <para>Shows the <link linkend="panels">effective permissions for the current user</link>.</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
      <para><link linkend="calculate">Calculates occupied space</link> by marked files and folders.</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
      <para>Internal <link linkend="krviewer">viewer and configurable editor.</link></para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
       <para>Offers a &cmdline_lnk; capable of running something in a terminal with a single click
             of a button.</para>
   </listitem>

  <listitem>
       <para>Completely supports drag'n'drop: drag from &konqueror; straight into a .tar.gz file, from
       &krusader;'s panel into the trash-bin, the desktop or into &konqueror;!</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
       <para><link linkend="unpacking-archives">Packs (or unpacks) files</link> into a single archive
       of your choice without typing a single command.</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
       <para><link linkend="test-archive">Tests the integrity of archives.</link>.</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
       <para><link linkend="compare-files">Compare files by content</link> (via external diff program
        such as &kompare;, &kdiff3_url;  or &xxdiff;).</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
      <para>Fully <link linkend="konfig-general">mimetype-aware</link> (with or without magic!).</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
      <para>Built-in Mount-Manager &mountman_lnk;.</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
      <para><link linkend="multi_rename">Krename</link> support, a very powerful
                                external batch renamer for &kde; 3.x.</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
     <para>&foldertabs_lnk;.</para>
  </listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</para>


<para>
